{
  "doc_id": "45730",
  "text": "Driven by environmental problems caused by using petroleum-derived polymers, the demand for the development of eco-friendly materials for agriculture, packaging, and coating industries has greatly increased [CITATION_1] . Due to their renewability and biodegradability, biopolymer materials made from natural resources such as proteins, cellulose, and polysaccharides are regarded as an attractive option in the development of environmentally friendly materials [CITATION_2] . It is reported that nanoparticles had an effect on protein-based films, but the tensile strength was still relatively poor [CITATION_3] . In order to further improve the mechanical properties of the protein film, we prepared a novel nanocomposite film modified with microcrystalline cellulose (MCC).",
